The Drakensberg Boys' Choir School is touted as South Africa's singing ambassadors. Editor's note: Please note this story may be upsetting to some viewers. JOHANNESBURG - The prestigious Drakensberg Boys Choir School has been accused of cultivating a culture of silence - and placing the protection of its image above the wellbeing of pupils. The claims come as a former pupil will go on trial in April for allegedly raping a younger boy. READ: Drakensberg Boys' Choir: Former pupil to go on trial for alleged rape The alleged incident is said to have taken place when both attended the school in 2018. School management insists the boys' safety is of utmost importance - and that it handled the incident appropriately. Barry Bateman has more in the video above